MOST POWERFULL ATTACK OF ALL - Remote system execution

- Hacker runs OS commands on web-server (Remotely)
- It can run any OS command
- typically hard to achieve for Hacker

PHP has SYSTEM execution function which allows to access OS.
Using anyone of these is considered SECURITY RED FLAG
- exec | passthru | popen | proc_open | shell_exec | system


HOW TO SOLVE?

- Avoid using these functions
- Use them after getting complete knowledge of system function
- you can use:
    escapeshellcmd($string);
    escapeshellarg($string);
to prevent from these attacks
    
